gov.usgs.edge.config

Class FKSetup

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.edge.config.FKSetup

  • public final class FKSetup
extends java.lang.Object
    FKSetup.java If the name of the class does not match the name of the field in the class you may need to modify the rs.getSTring in the constructor. This FKSetup template for creating a database database object. It is not really needed by the FKSetupPanel which uses the DBObject system for changing a record in the database file. However, you have to have this shell to create objects containing a database record for passing around and manipulating. There are two constructors normally given:
    1) passed a result set positioned to the database record to decode
    2) Passed all of the data arguments needed to build the same set of data.
    The FKSetup should be replaced with capitalized version (class name) for the file. fk should be replaced with the lower case version (for variables). Both the constructors use the "makeFKSetup(list of data args) to set the local variables to the value. The result set just uses the rs.get???("fieldname") to get the data from the database where the other passes the arguments from the caller.
    Notes on Enums :
    * data class should have code like :
    import java.util.ArrayList; /// Import for Enum manipulation
    .
    static ArrayList fieldEnum; // This list will have Strings corresponding to enum
    .
    .
    // To convert an enum we need to create the fieldEnum ArrayList. Do only once(static)
    if(fieldEnum == null) fieldEnum = FUtil.getEnum(JDBConnection.getConnection("DATABASE"),"table","fieldName");

    // Get the int corresponding to an Enum String for storage in the data base and
    // the index into the JComboBox representing this Enum
    localVariable = FUtil.enumStringToInt(fieldEnum, enumString);

        public FKSetup(int inID,
               java.lang.String loc,
               int role,
               double fkhpc,

               double beamwindow,

               int ftlen,

               int npoles,

               double kmax,
               int nk,
               java.lang.String args,
               java.lang.String refchan,
               java.lang.String channels,
               double snrLimit)
        create a row record from individual variables
        Parameters:
        inID - The ID in the database, normally zero for this type of construction
        loc - The key value for the database (same a name of database table)
        role - roleID assigned to compute this FK
        fkhpc - fk frequency space lower frequency limit
        fklpc - fk frequence space higher frequence limit
        beamwindow - Minimum number of seconds to put in each window
        beammethod - 0 is normal time domain stacking, others for nth root
        highpassfreq - Time domain highpass filter corner for preprocessing, and post processing
        latency - seconds to wait for real time data
        ftlen - The FTEST smoothing interval
        lowpassfreq - The Time domain lowpass filter corner for preprocessing and post processing
        npoles - Number of post of time domain filters
        npass - Number of passes of the time domain filters
        kmax - The maximum k value to consider in the FK space k = 2*pi*f/Vapp or w s in slowness
        nk - The number of evaluation points in FK space (must be odd) from -kmax to kmax is sampled over this many intervals
        args - Any additional arguments like -dbg
        refchan - The 12 character NSCL name of the reference channel, preceed with a '+' if it is to be used in calculation
        channels - The list of channels to use in the computation
        snrLimit - Signal to noise limit
